headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 34 points and nine assists after missing a game because of a sinus fracture, helping the Philadelphia 76ers beat the Charlotte Hornets 108-98 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid scores 34 points in return, helping the 76ers beat the Hornets 108-98

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 27 points, Darius Garland added 16 and the Cleveland Cavaliers moved to 15-1 at home with a 124-101 win on Friday night over the Milwaukee Bucks, who played for the first time since winning the NBA Cup.
headlines.shortLinkText: Donovan Mitchell scores 27 as Cavs improve to 15-1 at home, roll over NBA Cup champion Bucks 124-101

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — Jalen Williams scored a season-high 33 points, Shai Gilgeous-Alexander had 25 and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Miami Heat 104-97 on Friday night for their seventh straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Williams scores 33 points, Thunder remain red-hot by topping Heat 104-97
